@navis processing has to happen within the number of processing threads for several reasons:
a) we make processing threads configurable so a user is able to define how many cores should be used for querying
b) we need to ensure we don't exceed our max direct memory allocation, which we explicitly ask users to configure according to the number of processing threads they run.

@nishantmonu51 i think i see a race between task assignment and shutdown. can you confirm if this happened in a scenario where a call was made to shutdown one or more tasks? if that is the case then having a null check in runPendingTasks() would solve the issue.
also, this shouldn't have had any bad impact and overlord should have been able to make progress... did it continue to make progress after the error?
will send a PR to fix shortly if what i said above is true.

@fjy the rationale is the same as https://github.com/druid-io/druid/pull/2382 but adding the ability to filter based on datasources in addition to tiers. In @himanshug's case tiers were used as logical groups of datasources, but in our case we use tiers mainly for replica and time-based allocation, so it didn't fit our use case.

It will also reduce memory by not storing the additional tiers / datasources metadata in PathChildrenCache, which improves memory usage even further than #2382 did.

As a result it is now possible to have small dedicated brokers for a small subset of datasources, independently of the total size of the cluster
